# AI Safety Standards

**Input**: Treat user text as hostile. Max message length at gateway. Validate attachments against allowlist.

**System boundary**: Fixed system instructions; user content in delimited blocks. User text cannot override safety policy.

**Tools**: Allowlist only; map to risk tiers in `tool-risk-catalog.json`. Write/destructive tools require `ask` or `deny` — never silent execution.

**Injection**: Log suspected injection; block or escalate per policy mode. Test with red-team cases when changing prompts or tools. Adversarial fixtures live under `ai-runtime/eval/adversarial/` (see `prompt-evals.mdc`).

**RAG**: Version corpora; sanitize retrieved chunks; no executable content in context. Corpus allowlist: see `rag-pipeline.mdc`.

**Reference**: `templates/ai-runtime/guardrails/input-sanitization.md`, OWASP LLM section in `security.mdc`.
